In order to make it easy for a user to interact with the database we are creating two main views, one where they can search for policies given a set of standard SQL-type filters and a view that drills down the details of any given policy.

The contacts database functions almost independently of these policies but each policy can have a contact associated to it in several different ways.  A contact can be the referrer of the policy, they can bid on a policy, they may have been submitted (sent) a policy as well

fields.name: Trees for Life Journal
fields.description:
TFL would like to convert it's Trees for Life Journal at www.tfljournal.org from the current geeklog platform to a platform that would support a hybrid wiki/forum. We would like to know if Plone with a wiki and a forum is a good choice for this. Currently the TFL site is not using a wiki nor a forum.

TFL wants to add tools to this Journal site to allow collaboration by the community. A community of people that is interested in participating.

1). Wiki:
We want articles on beneficial trees and plants posted and edited by the community like a wiki . Some of the wiki articles would be unprotected for editing and others would be protected from editing.

2). Forum:
We also want the public to be able to ask questions that are answered by the community in a forum. FAQ etc.
 
3). Peer-reviewed Articles
This peer review process needs to be researched further and defined later:
Some of the articles would go through a peer-review process. This flow has not been articulated at this time. Currently we are doing peer-review of articles manually without the aid of peer-review software. We have been researching how others are attempting a wiki like peer review process but they have not had much success. It is possible to develop the site without this flow automated and continue the manual process until a time we can define the functionality fully for peer-review process.


The user would have just one login account for the wiki and for the forum.
The look would be different than the www.treesforlife.org so can a different skin be implement for this or does this site need to be hosted separately?
The way we see this working would be a mix of wiki and forum headings and summaries on the same page -- therefore a collage layout - not just a wiki or just a forum and it would need to have custom menus.


Example of a wiki/forum is The Student Room in the UK. They are using media wiki and vbulletin.
http://www.thestudentroom.co.uk/

Software that we consider helpful for this would be

zwiki
ploneboard
Plone Comments

* move cluemapper to deployments/ifpeople (or clients/ifpeople)

fields.name: It is not possible to set sharing permissions for groups
fields.description:
While conducting a search for a group using the search box on the sharing page for 'Work and Internship Opportunities', the search hung and the rest of the website was inaccessible for authenticated and unauthenticated users for about 10 minutes. Requests showed a 400 and a 500 error as it appeared the site was restarted. The site was accessible a couple of minutes later. This also appears to be an issue when searching for groups in site setup -> users and groups -> groups -> quick search. Individual user search also does not work in site set-up -> user and groups -> user search.

Gerry: This is likely a Salesforce integration issue. Perhaps we can find a fix by updating salesforce components? Should check with the maintainers of the integration products.

Franco. I did a search from the site set-up for both users and groups, and is working fine. The sharing tab is working as described though, i'm adding 2 hours on a task to try a deeper test and try to find a cause

Carlos. I am not very familiar with salesforce, but I have experienced similar problems with LDAP authentication (could be a bug in PAS). The solution I used was to override the default sharing view, to look specifically inside the LDAP user folder. This is a 3-4 hour task at most.

 Jebeze: I am now able to search for users and groups.  I added a user (u: testuser1, p:passcode1) to the group Generation Change and then gave sharing permissions to this Group in the project folder Generation Change (member permissions only), however, testuser1 does not have the ability to edit any pages in Generation Change, even when I add him to the sharing tab as well.

Carlos: By default, when you click the sharing tab on a folder, Plone shows not the actual sharing permissions for the folder, but of its default view. If you look carefully, you will find that you only gave testuser1 permission to modify the view, not the folder. Plone shows a message about this when you edit the roles, but it is easily missed, as you can see.

Carlos: A separate problem was found after this was solved: role sharing permissions for local roles (reader,contributor,editor) did not work. Turns out the workflow definition did not take those into account.

I conclude that we need to check with our script tot's products to see if they are all correct and then make an audit of their prod sqldb if they see this behavior repeat ( I saw the reports in tot's prod in the orders I checked and also in tot's dev so their db must be sane in case of seing odd behaviour we should do some sanitization)
